"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647113","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-12-06","<p>Details of the current unpaid advisers within the Government Art Collection can be found here: http://www.gac.culture.gov.uk/advisory-committee.html</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-12-06T17:11:05.55Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647113/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647113/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647113/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-28","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 28 November 2016 to Question 53795, what the (a) name, (b) job title and (c) responsibility is of each of the unpaid advisers currently based in the Government Art Collection of her Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","55209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647114","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-12-06","<p>The only current unpaid advisers within the First World War Centenary and Ceremonials Directorate are the members of the Centenary Advisory Group, who provide strategic oversight and challenge to the WWI Centenary programme; monitors delivery and progress and ensures that objectives remain current and appropriate. The group is made up of the following:</p><p> </p><ul><li>The Prime Minister’s Special Representative for the centenary of the First World War</li><li>One author</li><li>One academic</li><li>Three former Chief's of Defence Staff</li><li>Two historians</li><li>One director general of a British charity</li><li>Two MPs</li><li>One former Chief of the General Staff</li><li>One novelist</li><li>One playwright</li><li>Three peers</li><li>One public relations and philanthropy expert</li><li>One Dean</li><li>One print media expert</li><li>One former Defence Secretary</li><li>One expert in leadership development and cultural change</li><li>One history school teacher</li><li>Special Representatives for Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland</li></ul>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2016-12-06T17:13:58.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647114/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647114/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647114/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-28","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 28 November 2016 to Question 53795, what the (a) name, (b) job title and (c) responsibility is of each of the unpaid advisers currently based in the First World War Centenary and Ceremonials Directorate of her Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","55206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647115","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-12-06","<p>The only unpaid advisers within the Digital Economy Unit are a) the members of the Council for Digital Inclusion, whose are responsible for creating the right environment for motivating and enabling more people to make the most of the internet:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Two Directors/Managing Directors from leading UK retail banks<br> <br></li><li>One Director at a leading telecoms, broadband &amp; media provider<br> <br></li><li>One CEO of an accessibility charity<br> <br></li><li>One Commercial Director of a social housing organisation <br> <br></li><li>Two senior leaders from leading digital inclusion and skills charities<br> <br></li><li>One Senior leader from a local authority</li></ul><p> </p><p>And b) the Future Communications Challenge Group (FCCG), who advise DCMS on how the UK can lead in the development of 5G technology:</p><p> </p><ul><li>One President of a Learned Society<br> <br></li><li>Four Professors of Electronic and Radiocommunications Engineering<br> <br></li><li>Staff member at an Innovate UK sponsored Catapult project<br> <br></li><li>Two Heads of R&amp;D at telecoms companies <br> <br></li><li>One Vice President of an electronics components company <br> <br></li><li>One Head of Standards and Industrial Affairs with a communications device manufacturer <br> <br></li><li>One Chair of an International Radio body <br> <br></li><li>One Representative of a manufacturing trade body <br> <br></li><li>One CTO of a communications equipment manufacturer <br> <br></li><li>One Head of telecoms at an investment bank <br> <br></li><li>One Employee of a communications security company<br> <br></li><li>Two independent radiocommunications experts</li></ul><p> </p><p>In abiding by the DPA, to provide the name of each adviser would incur a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-12-06T17:53:19.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647115/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647115/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647115/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-28","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 28 November 2016 to Question 53795, what the (a) name, (b) job title and (c) responsibility is of each of the unpaid advisers currently based in the Digital Economy Unit of her Department.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","55204"
