"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647119","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-01","<p>Information about overseas exercises and formation size can be found in the attached table. Please note that for 2014 only limited data is held.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-12-01T16:05:43.357Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647119/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647119/answer","20161130-PQ11555_78020_Soames_Overseas_Exercises_ADOC_Input_O.xlsx","20161130-PQ11555_78020_Soames_Overseas_Exercises_ADOC_Input_O.xlsx","55182 - British Army conducted exercises overseas","55182 - British Army conducted exercises overseas","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647119/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-28","Army: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, in what foreign countries and in what formation the Army has conducted exercises in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","55182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647120","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-01","<p>The normal operating cycle of every ship involves them entering different readiness levels depending on their programmes and Departmental planning requirements.</p><p>It is Ministry of Defence policy not to publish details of the readiness states of individual Royal Navy vessels or types for the purpose of safeguarding national security.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-12-01T16:11:04.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647120/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647120/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-28","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent steps he has taken to ensure the readiness of the Type 45 destroyers.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","55170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647121","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-01","<p>Whilst UK military Unmanned Aerial Vehicles do not have a cargo capability, the Ministry of Defence is keeping all options under review.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-12-01T16:06:15.297Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647121/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647121/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-28","Syria: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the oral contribution of the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs of 28 November 2016, on the risks to RAF personnel of air drops of aid to Aleppo, what assessment he has made of the capacity of drones to undertake such air drops.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","55238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647122","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-01","<p>The Ministry of Defence continues to work with allies and partners to develop flexible and credible options to alleviate the humanitarian suffering in Aleppo.</p><p>The use of military aircraft to deliver aid presents high risks, not only to RAF personnel and aircraft, but to those on the ground in a dense urban area like Aleppo.</p><p>If it were possible to obtain the relevant permissions from the Syrian regime, then the World Food Programme would be able to use those permissions to get a safe route for the land delivery of the aid that is so desperately needed.</p><p>For air drops to be feasible, there is a need to identify clear drop zones, ensure safe access for the intended recipients, and to co-ordinate with authorities on the ground. Without this, air drops could result in civilian casualties. Flying RAF transport aircraft into hostile terrain and through the airspace around Aleppo would expose UK personnel to a severe risk of attack.</p><p>Nonetheless, this Government continues to keep all our options under review.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-12-01T16:07:13.3Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647122/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647122/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647122/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-28","Syria: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment he has made of the (a) feasibility and (b) risks of the RAF delivering aid through air drops to Aleppo; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","55239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647123","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-01","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) works hard to detect and deter theft and there are robust processes in place to raise awareness of the need for vigilance in all aspects of security. Just as theft occurs in wider society, the MOD is not immune and we actively encourage individuals to report any evidence of loss or suspicion of theft. It is important to note that in some cases of reported theft the property is later recovered. In the case of key assets however, MOD sites have a wide range of additional security measures to ensure their safety.</p><p>The weight of the full industrial kitchen and summer house has not been recorded.</p><p>In respect of the further detailed information requested this will take time to collate and I will write to the hon. Member shortly.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","55245 ; 55246 ; 55247 ; 55248","2016-12-01T16:12:12.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647123/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647123/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647123/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-28","Ministry of Defence: Theft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the information provided to the hon. Member for Liverpool, Wavertree and pursuant to the Answer of 8 November 2016 to Question 51845, what steps his Department has taken to (a) review stolen items on sale on eBay and (b) otherwise recover items stolen from its sites over the last year.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","55244"
