"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/644335","Department of Health","false","2016-11-30","<p>The following table outlines outturn and planned spend (which reflects the budgeted spend) in programme allocation growth in the periods 2014-15 and 2015-16. Figures are recorded in cash growth and not real growth terms:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>£ million</p></td><td><p>Planned Spend</p></td><td><p>Outturn</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>13,955</p></td><td><p>14,169</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>14,648</p></td><td><p>14,760</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-11-30T14:51:10.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/644335/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/644335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/644335/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-25","Health Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the (a) outturn, (b) planned spend and (c) budgeted spend in programme allocation growth for specialist commissioning was in each category in 2014-15 and 2015-16 in (i) cash and (ii) real terms.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","54960"
