"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643839","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-29","<p>As announced in Summer Budget 2015, and after more than four years of operation, the Equitable Life Payment Scheme is now closed. As a result the Payment Scheme is in the process of winding down. I will meet with a delegation of the All Party Parliamentary Group for Justice for Equitable Life Policy Holders.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2016-11-29T17:48:00.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643839/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643839/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-24","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Ministerial Statement of 18 November 2016, HCWS 269, if he will ensure that the £53.9 million due to policy holders who could not be paid will be allocated and distributed among other former Equitable Life policy holders.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","54772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643840","Church Commissioners","false","2016-11-28","<p>It has long been the practice of the Diocese of London for the Bishop to ordain all deacons, male and female, with Area Bishops ordaining priests in their local community.</p><p> </p>","Meriden","Dame Caroline Spelman",,"2016-11-28T16:22:05.57Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643840/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643840/answer",,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2016-11-24","Clergy: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, whether a Bishop of London has ordained a woman as a priest.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Bottomley","Worthing West","Sir Peter Bottomley","54893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643841","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-12-02","<p>The Government is aware of concerns about the quality of service provided by some managing agents. That is why we introduced legislation ensuring that property management agents belong to an approved redress scheme. There are Codes of Practice in place that can be applied by the courts to raise standards.</p><p>We are working with a number of partners, including the Law Commission, and are exploring whether further changes are required to address issues in this area.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2016-12-02T14:21:39.74Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643841/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643841/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-24","Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of regulation of long-term leasehold properties.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","54776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643842","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-29","<p>My Department has already published local authority allocations for each year of this Parliament as part of the four year funding offer. Birmingham City Council is among the 97% of councils that have accepted this offer. The government will soon consult on a statutory provisional local government finance settlement for 2017-18 in the normal way.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-11-29T17:15:42.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643842/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643842/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-24","Local Government Finance: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish funding allocations for Birmingham City Council.","false","Biography information for Jack Dromey","Birmingham, Erdington","Jack Dromey","54822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643843","Department of Health","false","2016-11-30","<p>The 2020 Dementia Challenge published in February 2015 made clear that, by 2020, we expect social care providers to provide appropriate training on dementia to all relevant staff.</p><p> </p><p>The Department estimates that over 100,000 social care workers have already received dementia awareness training. Newly appointed health care assistants and social care support workers, including those providing care and support to people with dementia and their carers, should undergo training as part of the national implementation of the Care Certificate.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","54721","2016-11-30T14:57:28.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643843/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643843/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-24","Home Care Services: Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment his Department has made of the level of dementia training provided to homecare workers delivering care to people with dementia.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","54720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643844","Department of Health","false","2016-11-30","<p>The 2020 Dementia Challenge published in February 2015 made clear that, by 2020, we expect social care providers to provide appropriate training on dementia to all relevant staff.</p><p> </p><p>The Department estimates that over 100,000 social care workers have already received dementia awareness training. Newly appointed health care assistants and social care support workers, including those providing care and support to people with dementia and their carers, should undergo training as part of the national implementation of the Care Certificate.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","54720","2016-11-30T14:57:28.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643844/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643844/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-24","Home Care Services: Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that all homecare workers receive dementia-specific training in every local authority.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","54721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643845","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-29","<p>The Government has not made a comparative assessment of trends in the levels of television programming by and for BME groups in the US and the UK. The Government is committed to diversity and social mobility in the broadcasting sector. Ministers have hosted a number of roundtables to encourage the broadcasting industry, and other creative industries, to involve more people from BME groups in making content both in front and behind the camera and to ensure that their content and programming serves all audiences. The Government has, as part of the BBC's updated Royal Charter, given the BBC new diversity duties to ensure it better serves diverse audiences including BME groups.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-11-29T11:21:21.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643845/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643845/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-24","Television: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what comparative assessment she has made of trends in levels of television programming by and for BME groups in the US and UK.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","54773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643846","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-29","<p>Ofcom has reported that in summer 2016, 88% of premises were capable of receiving speeds of more than 30Mbps. Thinkbroadband report current availability at 30Mbps for 91.42% of premises, with 92% being able to receive speeds above 24Mbps.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","54820","2016-11-29T13:04:18.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643846/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643846/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-24","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent estimate she has made of the number of households consistently receiving speeds of 30 megabits a second or above.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","54835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643847","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-29","<p>HM Forces Railcard is governed by a contract between the Association of Train Operating Companies (ATOC) and the Ministry of Defence. The provision of the railcard is a concession and not a condition of service. The terms and conditions are periodically reviewed by the Department and ATOC, and there are currently no plans to extend the current concession or establish a separate railcard for Service veterans.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","54836","2016-11-29T16:09:18.527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643847/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643847/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","Railways: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make it his policy to extend the criteria for the use of the HM Forces railcard to veterans.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","54837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643848","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-29","<p>I am delighted that Sir John Parker has submitted his independent report to inform the UK National Shipbuilding Strategy. The Chief Secretary and I received Sir John's report ahead of the Autumn Statement, as promised at the Budget 2016 (HC 901, article 2.284).</p><p> </p><p>The publication of Sir John's report was not delayed. The Government has today published Sir John's report and covering letter in full, and copies have been placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p><p>We will study Sir John's recommendations and will publish a full and considered response, and implementation plan, in spring 2017. This response will be the National Shipbuilding Strategy.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","54821","2016-11-29T16:17:16.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643848/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643848/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to publish the National Shipbuilding Strategy.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","54838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643849","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-29","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 24 November 2016 to Question number 53477 to the hon. Member for Portsmouth South (Mrs Flick Drummond).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-29T16:11:41.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643849/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643849/answer","Hansard Extract 24 November 2016, HOC 53477.docx","Hansard Extract 24 November 2016, HOC 53477.docx","Guided Weapons","Guided Weapons","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643849/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","Antiship Missiles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to replace the GWS 60/Harpoon Block 1C anti-ship missiles when they are withdrawn from Royal Navy service at the end of 2016.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","54839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643850","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-29","<p>I am delighted that Sir John Parker has submitted his independent report to inform the UK National Shipbuilding Strategy. The Chief Secretary and I received Sir John's report ahead of the Autumn Statement, as promised at the Budget 2016 (HC 901, article 2.284).</p><p> </p><p>The publication of Sir John's report was not delayed. The Government has today published Sir John's report and covering letter in full, and copies have been placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p><p>We will study Sir John's recommendations and will publish a full and considered response, and implementation plan, in spring 2017. This response will be the National Shipbuilding Strategy.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","54838","2016-11-29T16:17:16.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643850/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643850/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons publication of the National Shipbuilding Strategy has been delayed.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","54821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643851","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-30","<p>We have no record of Military helicopters flying over Manchester on 27 October 2016.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-11-30T16:04:51.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643851/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643851/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","Military Aircraft: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will investigate for what reasons military helicopters flying over Manchester on 27 October 2016 did so without running lights; and what communications were made between the Royal Air Force and Manchester City Council on that exercise.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","54891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643852","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-30","<p>On 26 October 2016 two Puma helicopters flew over Manchester as part of routine military activity. All processes were followed.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-11-30T16:04:06.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643852/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643852/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","Military Aircraft: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many helicopters flew over properties in Manchester on 26 October 2016 as part of a military exercise.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","54892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643853","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-30","<p>The estimated date of disposal for the Royal Citadel is 2024. The Department will ensure the appropriate amount of notice is given to the Crown Estate; however the date for this is not yet known.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-11-30T16:08:41.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643853/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643853/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","Ministry of Defence: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department plans to give the Crown Estate notice that it will be releasing its tenancy of the Citadel.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","54901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643854","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-30","<p>The annual running costs for Ministry of Defence (MOD) Caledonia, in each financial year from 2011-2012 to 2015-2016, are given below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Total Running Costs £ millions</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>6.92</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>7.12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>7.30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>7.94</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>8.30</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-11-30T16:03:11.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643854/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643854/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","MOD Caledonia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's report, a Better Defence Estate, published in November 2016, what the annual running costs were for MoD Caledonia in each financial year from 2011-12 to 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","54853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643855","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-29","<p>&quot;A Better Defence Estate&quot; is a military-led review. Ministry of Defence (MOD) officials wrote to Fife Council to inform them of the Department's plans to optimise the estate; as set out in &quot;A Better Defence Estate&quot;, and the impact upon MOD Caledonia. The letter sets out the potential disposal timeframe and invites engagement at official level. Officials will engage fully with Fife Council, prior to the sites disposal in 2022, in order to understand how the site could best support the local area.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","54928","2016-11-29T16:02:28.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643855/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643855/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-24","MOD Caledonia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with Fife Council on the disposal of MoD Caledonia.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","54854"
